---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

// Etzkowitz–Leydesdorff Triple Helix: University × Industry × Government overlap.
// Three intersecting circles with concrete SA / MEA examples in each region.

const W = 880, H = 600;
const cx1 = 340, cy1 = 250;  // University
const cx2 = 540, cy2 = 250;  // Industry
const cx3 = 440, cy3 = 410;  // Government
const r = 160;
---

<BaseLayout
  seo={{
    title: 'Triple Helix · Innovation Economics',
    description: 'University × Industry × Government overlap, with concrete South African and MEA examples populating each intersection.',
  }}
>
  <section class="container section">
    <nav class="breadcrumb">
      <a href="/economics">Innovation Economics</a> <span aria-hidden="true">/</span> <span>Triple Helix</span>
    </nav>

    <header data-reveal>
      <p class="eyebrow">Innovation Economics · Institutional overlap</p>
      <h1>The Triple Helix.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Etzkowitz and Leydesdorff: innovation emerges from the interaction of three institutional spheres
        — universities, industry, and government — each taking on roles traditionally held by the others.
        Universities commercialise. Firms do basic research. Governments take equity stakes. The model
        describes Silicon Valley, Cambridge UK, and Israel's tech ecosystem better than older linear
        models did. The interesting work happens in the overlaps; the centre is the rarest and most
        productive intersection.
      </p>
    </header>

    <figure class="chart" data-reveal>
      <svg viewBox={`0 0 ${W} ${H}`} role="img" aria-label="Triple Helix overlap with examples">
        <defs>
          <radialGradient id="g-uni" cx="50%" cy="50%">
            <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#4f46e5" stop-opacity="0.30" />
            <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#4f46e5" stop-opacity="0.10" />
          </radialGradient>
          <radialGradient id="g-ind" cx="50%" cy="50%">
            <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#0ea5e9" stop-opacity="0.30" />
            <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#0ea5e9" stop-opacity="0.10" />
          </radialGradient>
          <radialGradient id="g-gov" cx="50%" cy="50%">
            <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#f59e0b" stop-opacity="0.30" />
            <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#f59e0b" stop-opacity="0.10" />
          </radialGradient>
        </defs>

        <circle cx={cx1} cy={cy1} r={r} fill="url(#g-uni)" stroke="#4f46e5" stroke-width="1.5" />
        <circle cx={cx2} cy={cy2} r={r} fill="url(#g-ind)" stroke="#0ea5e9" stroke-width="1.5" />
        <circle cx={cx3} cy={cy3} r={r} fill="url(#g-gov)" stroke="#f59e0b" stroke-width="1.5" />

        {/* Sphere labels */}
        <text x={cx1 - 90} y={cy1 - 100} class="sphere-lbl" style="fill:#4f46e5">University</text>
        <text x={cx2 + 30} y={cy2 - 100} class="sphere-lbl" style="fill:#0ea5e9">Industry</text>
        <text x={cx3 - 50} y={cy3 + 130} class="sphere-lbl" style="fill:#f59e0b">Government</text>

        {/* Region examples — pure spheres */}
        <text x={cx1 - 110} y={cy1 - 20} class="ex">Public research</text>
        <text x={cx1 - 110} y={cy1} class="ex">Doctoral training</text>
        <text x={cx1 - 110} y={cy1 + 20} class="ex">CSIR &middot; HSRC</text>

        <text x={cx2 + 60} y={cy2 - 20} class="ex">Corporate R&amp;D</text>
        <text x={cx2 + 60} y={cy2} class="ex">JSE-listed labs</text>
        <text x={cx2 + 60} y={cy2 + 20} class="ex">MEA bank AI teams</text>

        <text x={cx3 - 80} y={cy3 + 80} class="ex">DSI &middot; DTIC</text>
        <text x={cx3 - 80} y={cy3 + 100} class="ex">National AI policy</text>
        <text x={cx3 - 80} y={cy3 + 120} class="ex">Public procurement</text>

        {/* Pairwise overlaps */}
        <text x={(cx1 + cx2) / 2} y={cy1 - 6} text-anchor="middle" class="overlap">Uni × Industry</text>
        <text x={(cx1 + cx2) / 2} y={cy1 + 12} text-anchor="middle" class="ex-overlap">Spinouts &middot; tech-transfer</text>
        <text x={(cx1 + cx2) / 2} y={cy1 + 28} text-anchor="middle" class="ex-overlap">Industry-funded chairs</text>

        <text x={(cx1 + cx3) / 2 - 30} y={(cy1 + cy3) / 2 - 10} text-anchor="middle" class="overlap">Uni × Gov</text>
        <text x={(cx1 + cx3) / 2 - 30} y={(cy1 + cy3) / 2 + 8} text-anchor="middle" class="ex-overlap">NRF grants</text>
        <text x={(cx1 + cx3) / 2 - 30} y={(cy1 + cy3) / 2 + 24} text-anchor="middle" class="ex-overlap">SARChI chairs</text>

        <text x={(cx2 + cx3) / 2 + 30} y={(cy2 + cy3) / 2 - 10} text-anchor="middle" class="overlap">Industry × Gov</text>
        <text x={(cx2 + cx3) / 2 + 30} y={(cy2 + cy3) / 2 + 8} text-anchor="middle" class="ex-overlap">SEZs &middot; tax credits</text>
        <text x={(cx2 + cx3) / 2 + 30} y={(cy2 + cy3) / 2 + 24} text-anchor="middle" class="ex-overlap">Sovereign equity</text>

        {/* Centre — all three */}
        <text x={(cx1 + cx2 + cx3) / 3} y={(cy1 + cy2 + cy3) / 3 - 6} text-anchor="middle" class="center">Triple Helix</text>
        <text x={(cx1 + cx2 + cx3) / 3} y={(cy1 + cy2 + cy3) / 3 + 12} text-anchor="middle" class="ex-center">Mission-led AI funds</text>
        <text x={(cx1 + cx2 + cx3) / 3} y={(cy1 + cy2 + cy3) / 3 + 28} text-anchor="middle" class="ex-center">Sovereign innovation co-investment</text>
      </svg>
      <figcaption>SA / MEA-anchored examples. The richer the overlap, the more permeable the boundaries between the three spheres.</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <section class="thesis" data-reveal>
      <p class="kicker">The thesis</p>
      <p>
        Triple Helix is operationally useful because it points to specific intervention levers:
        technology-transfer offices, sovereign innovation funds, university-affiliated incubators,
        mission-oriented public procurement. It can also produce concentrated outcomes if the helix is
        geographically narrow — one university region, one industry cluster, one tier of government.
        Broadening it across provinces, across historically disadvantaged universities, across both
        formal and informal sectors is itself a distributional choice. The question for any board engaging
        with university partnerships is which institutions and which geographies are inside the helix —
        and which are outside.
      </p>
    </section>

    <p class="back"><a href="/economics">← All models</a></p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .breadcrumb { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--color-ink-tertiary); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .breadcrumb a { color: var(--color-accent); text-decoration: none; }
  .eyebrow { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-xs); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.18em; color: var(--color-ink-tertiary); margin: 0 0 0.5rem; }
  h1 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); margin: 0 0 1rem; line-height: 1.1; }
  .lead { color: var(--color-ink-secondary); max-width: 70ch; margin: 0 0 2.5rem; line-height: 1.6; }

  .chart { margin: 0 0 2rem; padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--color-surface-raised); border: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle); border-radius: var(--radius-md); }
  .chart svg { width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }

  .sphere-lbl { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 22px; font-weight: 500; }
  .ex { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; fill: var(--color-ink-secondary); }
  .overlap { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; fill: var(--color-ink-primary); font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .ex-overlap { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; fill: var(--color-ink-secondary); }
  .center { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; fill: var(--color-accent); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .ex-center { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; fill: var(--color-ink-primary); }

  figcaption { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--color-ink-tertiary); margin: 1rem 0 0; letter-spacing: 0.04em; }

  .thesis { margin-top: 2rem; padding: 1.75rem; background: var(--color-surface-sunken); border: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle); border-left: 3px solid var(--color-ink-primary); border-radius: var(--radius-md); }
  .thesis .kicker { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.16em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-ink-tertiary); margin: 0 0 0.6rem; }
  .thesis p { margin: 0; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-ink-primary); }

  .back { margin-top: 2rem; }
  .back a { color: var(--color-accent); text-decoration: none; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.85rem; }
</style>
